		Sean Wargo is currently the President and Principal Consultant at The Market Sage, a consulting firm offering primary research and market opportunity assessments to consumer electronics firms. Before starting The Market Sage, Sean served as the Director of Industry Analysis at the Consumer Electronics Association for six years. In this role, Sean managed the data production and analysis of CEA's shipment data program. He was also a resident industry expert in CE, speaking and writing about products and trends based on consumer research, manufacturer shipment data, and time spent reading about and tinkering with technology. Sean has appeared in countless media outlets, including The New York Times, The LA Times, The Chicago Tribune, and The Wall Street Journal. Sean has over 10 years of experience working in the technology sector with the bulk of it spent as an analyst/ researcher covering retail and distribution trends for a broad array of CE and IT products. He graduated with a B.A. in Sociology/Research Methods from the University of Vermont and holds an MBA with a marketing concentration from George Mason University.<br>
